[{"id":30813,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Ionic Equilibrium","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>16</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>625</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Let, the solubility be&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi></math></p><p>Given that,&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi>sp</mi></msub><mfenced><mi>AgCN</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>16</mn></mrow></msup></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></msub><mfenced><mi>HCN</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AgCN</mi><mo>&#8652;</mo><munder><msup><mi>Ag</mi><mo>+</mo></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi></munder><mo>+</mo><munder><msup><mi>CN</mi><mo>-</mo></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi></munder><mo>&#160;&#160;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi>sp</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>16</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup